        },
        "subject": "LU-11449 osc: send RPCs for sparse writes",
        "message": "LU-11449 osc: send RPCs for sparse writes\n\nIf we check for full extents rather than dirty page count,\nwe will not send RPCs for small random writes until the\ncache limit is hit.\n\nThe solution is to start sending RPCs once there are enough\ndirty pages, regardless of whether or not they're\ncontiguous.\n\nBut we need to avoid splitting sequential writes from > 1\nwriter per stripe, so we have to check for greater than\nmax_pages_per_rpc.\n\nThe compromise chosen here is 4*max_pages_per_rpc, which\nwill work well for up to 4 simultaneous sequential writers\nand still flush random writes fairly quickly in most\nconfigs.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Iaa283e0fc904a23d229a4cec94b318a4e71748c5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
